[SN]TITLE[SN]
Woman shot by masked intruders in Newtownabbey

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A woman has been shot in the legs after two men forced their way into her home on the outskirts of north Belfast.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The woman, 47, and two men were in a flat at Ballyronan Park in Rathcoole, Newtownabbey, County Antrim, at about 19:45 GMT on Sunday when the masked men came in.
The woman fled from the flat but was shot in both legs outside. Her injuries are not thought to be life-threatening.
A 40-year-old man was also assaulted, sustaining minor injuries.
Police described the shooting as "utterly barbaric" and appealed for information.
